Rating: 2
Pleasant enough, certainly comfort food, but I was looking for something with a little more flavor. This just struck me as a wee bland. To be fair, I used equal parts hot and sweet Italian sausages (what I had on hand), a decidedly average home-made broth that was more vegetable than chicken and four sprigs of dried rosemary reconstituted in said broth for a few hours then minced. I don't doubt I'll make it again, but this is a dish I would make for myself when looking for something hearty, rather than serving to guests.

