Better if you cook the peas about half way in the stock first, then add the sauteed sausage, onions and potatoes. Otherwise I found the potatoes too mushy and the sausage overrcooked. I also added a jalapeno for spice and used my own unsalted stock and did not add any salt. The liguica I used was salty enough for the whole pot. Absolutely delicious.

