Rating: 3
You can't go wrong with soup on a snowy day. Using this recipe as inspiration, I doubled it with a full pound of linguica, a pound of split yellow & green peas, and 7 cups of broth. Borrowing from other recipes on the site, I added thyme, bay leaf, garlic, chopped celery and carrots. My tongue is still burning, but boy, was this good. A meal in itself.

Rating: 4
This was WONDERFUL. I used 3 Hillshire Farm Beef Hot Links that weighed 7 oz. (1/2 package). I followed the recipe with 3 exceptions: subbed 1/2 tsp. dried rosemary, added the potatoes at the same time as the peas, and added 1/8 tsp. crushed red pepper flakes to give it some ZING. Mine turned out somewhat watery, so I reduced it a bit at the end by simmering it, uncovered, for about 10 minutes. Next time I would replace a little of the broth with water, as it did taste a bit salty. DO try this--it SURE beats Healthy Choice.

