Rating: 3
This is definitely a keeper! It was very easy to make, hearty and yummy. My substitutions: chicken andouille sausage, sweet potato and low sodium vegetable broth. For my taste buds, I did not need additional salt or pepper. Although, I did need to add another 1½ cups of water to pot to make it more soupy. Next time: I will use only 1 or 2 sausages. That is more than enough for me. I like the idea of shredding the potato and I will try that. Also, I agree that the potatoes should be added with the peas.

